; Dungeon — level 1, dynamic layer (everything that changes during play).
; One record per line:
;
;   <kind> <type> <x> <z> [facing] [key=value ...]
;
; Kinds: monster, item, button (decorations are static — they go in the
; .map file). type names the asset/behavior: a monster's model is
; <type>.gltf. x/z are grid cells of level1.map, (0,0) top-left, x grows
; east, z grows south. facing is north/east/south/west (default south);
; buttons must face a solid wall. Examples of upcoming kinds:
;   item torch 4 1
;   button lever 9 5 east target=door_a
monster skeleton 6 1
monster blob 5 7
monster skeleton 5 11
monster mummy 6 12
monster blob 3 14
